<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,678,1026]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,313,787,811]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Remarks.</emphasis>
This synonym has been overlooked by previous authors, and there is no reference in tortricid literature to this name. There is a 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[474,704,822,846]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Phalaena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="allioniana">
<emphasis box="[474,704,822,846]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Phalaena allioniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described by Villers (
<number box="[952,1013,822,846]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1789.0">1789</number>
: 
<number box="[1025,1069,822,846]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="426.0">426</number>
) that has been considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Clerck, 1759" authorityName="Clerck" authorityYear="1759" box="[260,687,858,883]" class="Insecta" family="Dryophthoridae" genus="Aethes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hartmanniana">
<emphasis box="[260,505,859,883]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Aethes hartmanniana</emphasis>
(Clerck, 
<number box="[619,679,858,882]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1759.0">1759</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Perhaps this was an unjustified emendation (or misspelling) of Villers’ name. Apparently both names are dedicated to Allioni but there is no cross-reference in Fabricius and Villers publications. 
<bibRefCitation author="Herrich-Schaffer" box="[351,658,930,954]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refString="Herrich-Schaffer, G. A. W. (1856) Index alphabetico-synonymicus ad Vol. I - V. Pp. (1) 24, (2) 64, (3) 34, (4) 48, (5) 52. Systematische Bearbeitung der Schmetterlinge von Europa, 6. Regensburg." type="journal article" year="1856">
Herrich-Schäffer (
<number box="[556,613,930,954]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1856.0">1856</number>
(
<number box="[631,648,930,954]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="4.0">4</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number box="[670,684,930,954]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="3.0">3</number>
) listed this name as “(
<taxonomicName box="[940,1047,931,955]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Pyralis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="allionana">
<emphasis box="[940,1047,931,955]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">allionana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) F. 
<taxonomicName box="[1093,1225,931,955]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" rank="variety" variety="decimana">
<emphasis box="[1093,1225,931,955]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">v. decimana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”, meaning that he considered 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius" authorityName="Fabricius" box="[279,585,966,990]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Pyralis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="allionana">
<emphasis box="[279,474,966,990]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Pyralis allionana</emphasis>
Fabricius
</taxonomicName>
a variation of 
<taxonomicName authority="Denis and Schiffermuller, 1775" authorityName="Denis and Schiffermuller" authorityYear="1775" box="[748,1315,966,990]" class="Insecta" family="Dryophthoridae" genus="Aethes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decimana">
<emphasis box="[748,939,966,990]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Aethes decimana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Denis" box="[953,1307,966,990]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refString="Denis, M. &amp; Schiffermuller, I. (1775) Ankundung eines systematisches Werkes von den Schemetterlinge der Wiener Gegend herausgegeben von einigen Lehrern am k. k. Theresianum. Wien, Austria, i + 323 pp, 3 pls." type="book" year="1775">
Denis and Schiffermüller, 
<number box="[1250,1307,966,990]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1775.0">1775</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and this is the interpretation we propose to follow.
</paragraph>
